Specific responsibilities of the commission shall include implementation of:
Programs to provide maximum flexibility for students in transferring from one (1) school or college to another, including changes which minimize or eliminate loss of credit;
Aggressive efforts to expand the Work/Study Scholarship Program available through the Kentucky Higher Education Assistance Authority;
Continuing exploration of cooperation between businesses and state agencies, and businesses and university or vocational school job training programs; and
Scheduling of meetings of the commission, to be held at least three (3) annually, to accomplish these purposes.
